02:07.491 --> 02:09.910
All right, what number
did you give the agency?

02:09.911 --> 02:11.570
I gave them everyone's number.

02:11.571 --> 02:14.240
Uh, my phone, your phone,
the house phone, the work phone.

02:14.241 --> 02:17.466
Everything except Victoria's
dealer and Vince's bookie.

02:18.451 --> 02:20.450
Maybe they hated
our photo album, huh?

02:20.451 --> 02:23.030
Oh, God... I never should have
included that old-timey picture

02:23.031 --> 02:24.910
we did at Six Flags.

02:24.911 --> 02:27.570
Now I bet they think
we're really wanted.

02:27.571 --> 02:29.990
Sweetie, it's only been a week.

02:29.991 --> 02:31.650
The last thing they said was,
"Be patient,

02:31.651 --> 02:32.950
these things take time."

02:32.951 --> 02:34.360
What the hell kind
of advice is that

02:34.361 --> 02:36.820
to give to an expectant parent?

02:36.821 --> 02:39.530
Mol, a real baby
takes nine months.

02:39.531 --> 02:41.570
The least we could do
is give them two weeks.

02:41.571 --> 02:43.150
Two weeks?

02:43.151 --> 02:44.740
I thought you wanted a baby.

02:44.741 --> 02:46.200
Okay, if you're not all in,
tell me now

02:46.201 --> 02:48.490
because I will
raise it on my own.

02:48.491 --> 02:50.110
Take it easy, okay?

02:50.111 --> 02:52.990
We're both on
the same side here.

02:52.991 --> 02:54.820
Then why aren't you
all crazy like me?

02:54.821 --> 02:56.450
Because I leave the house.

02:56.451 --> 02:57.780
You're in this cage all day

02:57.781 --> 02:59.910
pacing around like
that cross-eyed zebra at the zoo

02:59.911 --> 03:01.700
we sneak marshmallows to.

03:01.701 --> 03:05.031
Poor little Stewart,
he don't see right.

03:06.031 --> 03:07.410
What do you say

03:07.411 --> 03:10.320
we get the hell out of
here and take a walk.

03:10.321 --> 03:12.780
You're right.
I'm sorry I'm acting like this.

03:12.781 --> 03:15.030
I'm not. Just shows
how much you want this

03:15.031 --> 03:16.861
and what a good mom
you're gonna be.

03:21.201 --> 03:23.360
Fresh air.

03:23.361 --> 03:25.860
Blue sky.
What a day.

03:25.861 --> 03:28.070
All right.
I'm good.

03:28.071 --> 03:30.030
No, you don't.
No, no, no.

03:30.031 --> 03:32.530
Come on, we should at least
make it down to the sidewalk.

03:36.031 --> 03:37.200
Did you bring the house key?

03:37.201 --> 03:39.410
Me? No, you're the one
who dragged me out here.

03:39.411 --> 03:41.110
I was happy inside.

03:41.111 --> 03:42.530
What are we supposed to do now?

03:42.531 --> 03:44.530
I don't know. All I know is
our baby is calling

03:44.531 --> 03:46.201
on the other side of that door.

03:49.611 --> 03:50.740
Don't hang up!

03:50.741 --> 03:52.700
Don't hang up!
Don't hang up!

03:56.031 --> 03:59.530
Hello? Hello?

03:59.531 --> 04:03.201
No, Vince, we do not
need anything from Costco.

04:11.701 --> 04:12.860
Ten years on the job.

04:12.861 --> 04:15.360
I never had to kick in
a door until it was my own.

04:15.361 --> 04:16.781
Does that ankle
look swollen to you?

04:18.151 --> 04:19.820
They both do.

04:19.821 --> 04:21.610
But I'm guessing
it's water retention.

04:21.611 --> 04:23.570
Yeah, I think it's
all that salt you eat.

04:23.571 --> 04:25.280
Not in the mood, Carl.

04:25.281 --> 04:27.320
Hey, listen, we both
have to watch our sodium.

04:27.321 --> 04:28.410
Look how fat my fingers are.

04:28.411 --> 04:29.611
Can't even wear my thumb ring.

04:29.816 --> 04:32.240
Get out.

04:32.241 --> 04:34.910
It's just this whole baby thing
has got us on edge, you know?

04:34.911 --> 04:36.610
I'm trying to be
strong for Molly,

04:36.611 --> 04:39.450
but I'm going
just as nuts as she is.

04:39.451 --> 04:41.110
Well, you know
what I always say.

04:41.111 --> 04:42.360
It'll happen...

04:42.361 --> 04:43.741
when it happens.

04:45.151 --> 04:46.360
Really?

04:46.361 --> 04:47.740
Is that when it happens, Carl?

04:47.741 --> 04:48.741
When it <i>happens?</i>

04:50.741 --> 04:52.611
Well, not with that attitude.

04:53.911 --> 04:55.360
Look, you don't know
what we're going through.

04:55.361 --> 04:58.030
It's like slow torture waiting
for that phone to ring.

04:58.031 --> 04:59.200
All right.

04:59.201 --> 05:00.650
I can see that this
is tearing you apart,

05:00.651 --> 05:02.320
and I know you don't
want to hear this, but...

05:02.321 --> 05:04.700
I think you may need to
talk to a professional.

05:04.701 --> 05:06.610
Like a therapist?

05:06.611 --> 05:07.700
No, better.

05:07.701 --> 05:08.700
My psychic.

05:08.701 --> 05:10.700
Get out of here.

05:10.701 --> 05:12.610
I'm telling you, man,
Madame Vianne is the real deal.

05:12.611 --> 05:14.610
She knows all, she sees all.

05:14.611 --> 05:16.490
And she's a life coach.

05:16.491 --> 05:19.411
And if you need anything
notarized, bring that, too.

